The paper discusses security and scalability challenges in the context of IoT and proposes a new framework that uses blockchain technology to address these challenges. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a "data marketplace" and financial transactions, which could fall under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. The use of blockchain technology also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of encryption and access control, which could fall under the cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories, respectively.
